did.unittitle: Rockefeller University collection of The Medical Letter publication

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: Martin A. Rizack is an editor for THE MEDICAL LETTER. THE MEDICAL LETTER on Drugs and Therapeutics is an independent, non-profit publication providing unbiased critical evaluation of Drugs in terms of their effectiveness, adverse effects and possible alternative medications.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Published printed material supplied by non-profit publication.

Material consists of files used in preparing articles for THE MEDICAL LETTER for the years 1959 to 1977; each file consisting of drafts of the article, letters from consultants and manufacturers; and copies of published articles from the medical and scientific literature which were used in preparing the articles. Some in folders and some in envelopes.
Additional materials are available through 1985 (Boxes 398-688) which have received standard processing, and are described in an available PDF.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition note
acqinfo.p: Initial Date received/inventoried : July 29, 1982. Rockefeller Archive Center receives additions to the collection periodically.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records are open for research twenty-five years after their creation. Select files restricted as noted. Use agreement is required prior to providing access. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.
